# IERG4210 Web Security Project — Full-Stack E-Commerce Application

**Student ID:** 1155192972  
**Course:** IERG4210 — Web Security, CUHK  
**Live Site:** [https://s14.ierg4210.iecuhk.cc](https://s14.ierg4210.iecuhk.cc)  
**Server:** Azure VM (Ubuntu 24.04 LTS) · `20.74.81.143`

***

## Overview

A production-deployed, security-hardened full-stack e-commerce web application built from scratch. The project covers the complete software engineering lifecycle — from database schema design and REST API development to cloud deployment, reverse proxy configuration, and TLS certificate provisioning. All security mechanisms including CSRF protection, secure session management, HTTPS enforcement, and input validation are implemented **from first principles** without relying on high-level security frameworks.

***

## System Architecture

```
User Browser (HTTPS)
        │
        ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────┐
  │         Nginx               │
  │  - Port 80 → 301 redirect   │
  │  - Port 443 SSL termination │
  │  - Static file serving      │
  │  - Reverse proxy to :3001   │
  │  - X-Forwarded-Proto header │
  └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                 │ proxy_pass
                 ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────┐
  │      Express.js (PM2)       │
  │  - REST API routes          │
  │  - Session middleware       │
  │  - CSRF middleware          │
  │  - Auth middleware          │
  │  - Multer file uploads      │
  └──────────────┬──────────────┘
                 │
                 ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────┐
  │         SQLite DB           │
  │  - categories               │
  │  - products                 │
  │  - users                    │
  └─────────────────────────────┘
```

***

## Project File Structure

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `server.js` | Main Express application — routes, middleware, session, CSRF |
| `database.js` | SQLite database initialization and schema setup |
